EXTRACTED VALUE: Turok offers a few entertaining hours of play, but isn't spectacular enough to keep you coming back long after you've slain the last dinosaur.
Although TimeShift brings a neat gimmick to the table, that's about all it brings.
Even though the wingman mechanics and canyon races don't quite pan out, it's still a stylish and enjoyable street racer.
Sadly, match types come in just two flavors: artifact raids or kill sprees, which makes $60 seems extortionate. [Aug 2007, p.78]
